# Python & LangGraph Patterns

## Project Layout

- `app/agents/` — graphs, nodes, prompts (no business logic in routes)
- `app/models/` — Pydantic schemas only
- `app/services/` — LLM, memory, search (injectable, mockable)

## LangGraph

- Use `LinkAidState` with `add_messages` reducer
- SqliteSaver checkpointer in dev; compile graph once at startup
- Router node returns intent; specialist nodes return partial state
- `format_response` node enforces `LinkAidResponse` before END

## LLM (Groq)

```python
# Structured output + retry
response = await llm.with_structured_output(LinkAidResponse).ainvoke(messages)
```

- System prompts in `app/agents/prompts/` as `.md` or constants
- Log model, latency, token usage to metadata field

## FastAPI

- Versioned routes: `/api/v1/...`
- Dependency injection for graph, memory, settings
- Return Pydantic models; never raw dicts from endpoints
